The paper deals with query evaluation and containment under constraints, which are fundamental topics in database theory and artificial intelligence. The use of tuple-generating dependencies (TGDs) and equality generating dependencies (EGDs) is common in database theory, which suggests that cs.DB is a likely sub-category. The paper also introduces a condition under which EGDs do not interact with TGDs, which is a topic related to ontology languages and description logics, indicating that cs.LO and cs.AI are also likely sub-categories. The paper provides complexity bounds for the problem of conjunctive query evaluation, which is a topic related to computational complexity, suggesting that cs.DS and cs.CC are also possible sub-categories.
